-- Czech Stocks: Central European Media, New World Resources Move
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-04-03T14:58:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/czech-stocks-central-european-media-new-world-resources-move.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell for a second day, sliding 0.3 percent to 965.2 at its close
in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV)   climbed
5.2 percent, the most in seven weeks, to 146.5 koruna. Bank of
America Corp. analysts said in a report yesterday that Time
Warner Inc. may increase its stake in the broadcaster this year.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, added 1.4 percent to 133 koruna, making it the
third-best performer in the PX benchmark today. The company’s
OKD AS unit called off a strike warning after an agreement on
wages was reached, CTK public newswire reported late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
